Go to now, ye that say. Today or to morrow we will go into such a city, and
continue there a year, and buy and sell, and get gainï¼š Whereas ye know not
what shall be on the morrow. For what is your life? It is even a vapour, that
appeareth for a little time, and then vanisheth away. For that ye ought to
say. If the Lord will, we shall live, and do this, or that.
